  <RulesElement name="Mounted" type="Weapon Property" internal-id="ID_FMP_WEAPON_PROPERTY_35" source="Core">
A mounted weapon is most effective when you use it while riding a mount. When you use such a weapon while not mounted, you take a -2 penalty to attack rolls with it. While you are mounted, your charge attacks with the weapon deal 1[W] extra damage.
</RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Reaching" type="Weapon Property" internal-id="ID_FMP_WEAPON_PROPERTY_34" source="Core" revision-date="8/13/2010 6:23:39 PM">
You gain +1 reach with melee attacks using a reaching implement.
   </RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Blinking" type="Weapon Property" internal-id="ID_FMP_WEAPON_PROPERTY_33" source="Core" revision-date="8/13/2010 6:24:16 PM">
When you hit with a teleportation attack power, you have concealment until the start of your next turn.
   </RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Mobile" type="Weapon Property" internal-id="ID_FMP_WEAPON_PROPERTY_32" source="Core" revision-date="8/13/2010 6:24:18 PM">
When you hit with an attack using a mobile implement, you can shift as a minor action before the end of your turn.
   </RulesElement>
